My application is simple scaffold with a text widget. I want when I launch the application or open a new page, focus on a text or even on the title of my appBar and not the backButton for a new page.
On Android it does not focus directly, but only after a delayed.  And for iOS never focus either directly or with a delayed.

### Simple page with text widget focused after 1 second delayed

**Steps to Reproduce**
Using the following example app:
<details>
<summary>code sample 1</summary>

```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(const MaterialApp(
    title: 'SimpleApp',
    home: Page(),
  ));
}

class Page extends StatefulWidget {
  const Page({
    Key? key,
  }) : super(key: key);

  @override
  _PageState createState() => _PageState();
}

class _PageState extends State<Page> {
  var display = false;

  @override
  void initState() {
    super.initState();

    WidgetsBinding.instance?.addPostFrameCallback((_) {
      Future.delayed(const Duration(seconds: 1)).then((onValue) => setState(() {
            display = true;
          }));
    });
  }

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: const Text('My page'),
      ),
      body: Column(
        mainAxisAlignment: MainAxisAlignment.center,
        children: [
          if (display == true) ...[
            Center(
              child: Semantics(
                focused: true,
                child: const Text('I want the focus !'),
              ),
            ),
          ],
        ],
      ),
    );
  }
}
```
</details>

1. Open the above app with talkback enabled on an Android device.
2. Wait 1 Second
3. The text "I want the focus" is appear and directly focused

If you change delayed time to 0 seconds, the text "I want the focus" appear directly and not focused. The focused stay on appBar title.

Not working on iOS, widget is never focused with the semantics focused to true.

### Page navigation, focused on appBar title from a new page

My primary objective is that each time a new page is opened, we focus on the title of the appBar and not on the backButton. But without delayed impossible to put the focus on the title of the appBar.


**Steps to Reproduce**
Using the following example app:

<details>
