> I tried your last code sample (copied below for clarity) with and without cacheExtent but I still see the scroll bar to jump (after about 15 seconds of expansion)

I see. In your video, you scroll far away from that top widget, so it is not updating with the expanded height. Since it is out of view and beyond the cache extent, the lazy loading list does not rebuild it, it doesn't need to because we can't see it. But in the meantime, your timer based _expandedHeight is still growing. When you scroll back up towards the top widget, it updates the _expandedHeight all at once so you see the jump. Do you mean to always have it growing? If so, see the solution below. If not, you may want to stop incrementing the height when the top widget is not visible.

