---

Here is what I came up with, using a CustomScrollView is probably most appropriate for your use case, separating your growing leading item from the rest. That way the rest of the list is built lazily, and the size of the expanding widget will continue smoothly.

Of course, since the top widget continues to grow, the scroll view will also be moving since it is continually expanding. 

If you do not want this behavior, then the earlier solutions should suit, but I would recommend not incrementing the size while the top widget is not visible, otherwise it will continue to 'grow' but update all at once later when the widget comes back into view, causing the undesired jump.

```dart
import 'dart:async';
import 'dart:math';
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
