Yes. The first item expands when Bluetooth LE messages arrive with new time series data. So in effect it is always able to expand, even when not visible or in the active region of the ListView. The scrollbar should always be reflecting this actual length.

> Of course, since the top widget continues to grow, the scroll view will also be moving since it is continually expanding.

I have a work around for this. Super hacky, but:
1. I instead of append to the top, append to the bottom of the list. 
2. wrap the scroll view in a 180 transform, so that bottom becomes top
3. flip each List item 180 degrees as well.  

